John R. Strangfeld, 35 years old, was named to the new post of chairman of Prudential Investment Corp./Europe, a unit of this financial services company.
Mr. Strangfeld will be based in London and will manage Prudential's corporate finance operation, PIC Capital Group, also based there.
In addition, he will be responsible for expanding the company's role in European investment management.
He had been a senior vice president of Prudential Capital Corp., a subsidiary of the Prudential Investment Corp. unit.
Prudential Investment has about $200 billion under management, "the overwhelming majority" of which is in the U.S., a spokesman said. 

